message.content: A 65-year-old male with a history of COPD presents with a productive cough, fever, and shortness of breath, suggestive of bacterial pneumonia.
A 63-year-old Caucasian male with a history of COPD presents with fever, productive cough, and dyspnea for 3 days, suggestive of bacterial pneumonia.
A 65-year-old male with a history of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease presents with fever, productive cough, and shortness of breath, suggestive of bacterial pneumonia.
A 65-year-old male with a history of COPD presents with fever, cough productive of purulent sputum, and shortness of breath consistent with community-acquired bacterial pneumonia.
